        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 4:21PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles north of Amarillo, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
